These two lines are pretty overwhelming to read, lots of "givenUnitWithSuicideOnHit", IMO the method names blur together and it becomes hard to tell exactly which API overload is being invoked where.
An intermediate variable could help, eg:
final var unitType = givenUnitTypeWithSuicideOnHit(typeName, suicideOnHit);
return givenUnitWithSuicideOnHit(unitType);

